i## How to Set Up		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i**Hardware Setup:**		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iConnect the serial ports of both boards. The Raspberry Pi's serial		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iport uses Pin 8 (TX) for transmission and Pin 10 (RX) for reception (check		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ipinout.xyz		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i). The Tinker Board's serial port also uses Pin 8 (TX) and Pin 10 (RX).		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iUse two jumper wires to connect:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i- Raspberry Pi Pin 8 → Tinker Board Pin 10		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i- Raspberry Pi Pin 10 → Tinker Board Pin 8		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iIf the boards use separate power supplies (like mine), connect a third		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ijumper wire between their GND pins (Pin 6 on both boards). This		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iensures a common ground reference for voltage level consistency.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i**Software Setup:**		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iInstall pppd on both devices:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  # Debian-based (Tinker Board)		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  apt-get install ppp		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  # Arch-based (Raspberry Pi)		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  pacman -S ppp		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iStart pppd services:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  # Run on one board		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  pppd -detach noauth /dev/ttyS1 1000000 172.18.233.1:172.18.233.2 local nocrtscts xonxoff		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  # Run on the other board		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  pppd -detach noauth /dev/ttyS1 1000000 172.18.233.2:172.18.233.1 local nocrtscts xonxoff		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i**Parameter Explanation:**		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i- `-detach` : Keep process in foreground		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i- `noauth` : Disable authentication		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i- `/dev/ttyS1` : Serial device path (default for RPi 3B & Tinker		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  Board)		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i- `1000000` : Baud rate (tested maximum stable speed)		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i- `172.18.233.1:172.18.233.2` : Local IP : Peer IP		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i- `local` : Disable modem control lines		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i- `nocrtscts` : Disable hardware flow control		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i- `xonxoff` : Enable software flow control		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
